><hr size=1> Best of the Best Event Rule Sheet<br>
Enchanter 54+ <br>
<br>
<br>
Single Elimination 1 vs. 1 competition for all rounds but final round.<br>
Final round (to determine 1st and 2nd place on both test and live) will be 2 out of 3 matches. <br>
<br>
<br>
Dates: August 27th through September 13th on Live Servers, times will be posted at least 48 hours in advance.<br>
The final is on the Test Server September 16th at Noon. All possible servers will be represented. <br>
<br>
<br>
Spectator and General Rulings <br>
<br>
Due to the use of NPCs in this event Spectators will not be allowed to attend. Any spectators found in the arena will be removed and asked not to return. <br>
<br>
Guides and GM's are considered judges and therefore restricted from being attacked. Anyone found attacking a GM or Guide may be banished from the Arena or death touched without warning.<br>
<br>
The Arena is off limits to unauthorized PvP 15 minutes before and 15 minutes after the event. This is to ensure that the contestants and spectators are safe.<br>
<br>
The EULA and Rules of Conduct bind all spectators and contestants as set forth by SOE and Verant Interactive, Inc.<br>
<br>
Spectators and Contestants found breaking the rules could have actions taken against their account including suspension or possible banning.<br>
<br>
<br>
General Combatant Rules <br>
<br>
Sign-up for the event will begin one half-hour before the scheduled event, and close at the scheduled time of the event start as posted on Harpy's Head Tavern events area. Contestants wishing to compete in the event must be in the arena prepared to compete before the end of the sign-up period. A shout will be made in the Arena to signify the start of sign-up, and another shout made to signify the close of sign-up.<br>
<br>
The top of the throne, in the throne, or behind the throne is off limits to the combatants during the matches. The four fire pots are also off limits to the combatants. Use of these areas in match combat will lead to contestants being disqualified.<br>
<br>
Starting positions are in the center four squares of the stage area, each contestant will be summoned to center of the stage at start of match.<br>
<br>
All participants will be debuffed before the match.<br>
<br>
Weapons with the following spell effects attached to them will not be allowed in Best of the Best Series; Knockback, Fear, Invisibility, and shrink.<br>
<br>
The use of &quot;Right Click&quot; items is not permitted unless specifically stated otherwise in the Class Specific Rules.<br>
<br>
The following spell types may not be used in any of the Best of the Best Series: <br>
<br>
Any form of Fear.<br>
Gravity Flux or Invert Gravity<br>
Any form of translocation spell (Example shadow step) <br>
The following item types will not be allowed in the Best of the Best Series:<br>
<br>
<br>
Any type of Artifact items. (Example Butcher Block Hammer.)<br>
Any type of Hit Point regeneration effect items. (Example Fungi Tunic) <br>
In the event that the combat exceeds 15 minutes of real time, then the Event Staff may cast an AoE Snare spell on the contestants, and the contestants are to remain snared till end of match.<br>
<br>
The owner of the account must play the character, no &quot;Ringers&quot; will be allowed. Any account found with someone besides the registered and original owner of the account playing that character is breaking the EULA as set forth by Verant Interactive.<br>
<br>
Any use of exploits or bugs will result in immediate disqualification from the event, and is a break in the rules of conduct as set forth on www.everquest.com.<br>
<br>
Rallos Zek Specific rule: There shall be no looting of any item at an event, this includes spectators. Anyone that is found player killing for profit at an event may have actions taken on his or her account.<br>
<br>
<br>
Class Specific Rules <br>
<br>
There is no entry fee for this event and the only prizes will be titles awarded to the winners. Title for winning at the server level will be the level 51 title for Enchanter &quot;the Illusionist&quot;. The title for the 3 runners up on Test Server Finals will be the level 56 title &quot;the Beguiler&quot;. The grand champion of the Test Server Finals shall have the level 60 title given to him on his own server &quot;the Phantasmist&quot;.<br>
<br>
The object for the Enchanters will be be to kill the opposing Enchanter by any means necessary. This includes the use of pets, spells. melee, or charming of NPCs.<br>
<br>
The stage area will be set up with 6 NPCs. One in front of each of the firepots on the stage and 2 on the edge (either side) of the platform. The NPCs will be killed and reset following each match. Both contestants will be summoned to the center of the stage, which is out of the aggro range of the NPCs. Once summoned each contestant will be asked if ready. After contestants acknowledge they are ready a 30 second buffing time will start. All contestants will be safe (non aggro) inside the 4 tiles around the direct center of the platform. Any movement outside this area will cause the NPCs to attack. A match will not be restarted if a contestant causes a NPC to attack by moving after signifying the contestant is ready to compete. No spells will be cast on opposing Enchanter or NPCs during the 30 second buffing period.<br>
<br>
The NPCs used for the event will be level 43-47 with ample hit points (since object is to use them and not to kill them). The resists will be average for the level of the NPC and they will assist each other in need.<br>
<br>
Once a match reaches 5 minutes the Events Staff will spawn an additional NPC in the center of the stage, and will continue to spawn more in 45-second increments.<br>
<br>
All Armor and Weapons available to the contestant's class will be allowed. Unless it has, an effect stated in General Combat rules as unusable.<br>
<br>
The &quot;right click&quot; on the Enchanter Epic weapon (Staff of Serpent) is allowed in this event.<br>
<br>
The use of Mesmerization spells may only be directed at NPCs and Pets in this event.<br>
<br>
The following fear spells will not be allowed: <br>
<br>
Fear<br>
Invoke Fear<br>
Trepidation<br>
Chase the Moon<br>
<br>
The following Invisibility and translocation spells will not be allowed: <br>
<br>
Invisibility<br>
Improved Invisibility<br>
Gate<br>
<br>
The following other spells will not be allowed: <br>
<br>
Sentinel<br>
<br>
All other spells are allowed to be used during this event, unless stated as disallowed in the General Combat rules. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Test Server Finals<br>
(To be held on September 16th at 12 noon PST, registration to start at 11:15 am PST) <br>
<br>
Those champions who go to Test Server are bound by additional rules: The character used for the event cannot adventure on Test for any reason. Handing off even the smallest items to a player on Test is considered duplication, resulting in a warning against the account, and loss of that item on your home server. Those found extremely abusing this rule may have further action taken against the account at the discretion of the EQ development team.<br>
<br>
The transfer of characters to Test is midnight (give or take an hour) PST the night before the main event.<br>
<br>
The Arena will be closed to the public several hours before the main event. The only characters allowed in the Arena on Test for the main event will be the champions, the judges of the event and the event staff, other members of Verant Interactive, and members of the press who signed up with the Events Staff at least three days in advance via email at EventMaster@Station.Sony.com. <br>
<br>
<br>
All other characters on Test found in the Arena during the main event will be summoned out of the zone and bound so they cannot return. If a second character is found to enter the Arena for any reason, it could be considered disruption and subject to action taken against the account.<br>
